CatDescriptText: Related image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper. February 13, 1971, page 23 reads: "RECEIVING LINE-Wearing her gorgeous inaugural gown, a Malcolme Starr original, the Hon. C DeLores Tucker, Secretary of the Commonwealth of Pennsylvania, stands in receiving line at the recent reception given in her honor by the Women's Auxiliary of the Pittsburgh Branch NAACP. Held in the Terrace Room of the William Penn Hotel..." --Harris photo
TitMainTitle: Men and women, including Harold Hayes second from left, Bill Tucker, Jean Milko, C. DeLores Tucker, Secretary of the Commonwealth of Pennsylvania, Eugene Coon, Mary Gloster, Duane Darkins and Reverend LeRoy Patrick on right in rear, at NAACP Women's Auxiliary event at the William Penn Hotel
